{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606111","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606111"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:08:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:08:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15895"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15895","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15895"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8586"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72059"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8586","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8586"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15895"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57529"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3618"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"10624"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20579"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20582"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72059","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72059"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring pregnancy, oestrogen production requires cooperation between maternal, placental and fetal tissues. The placenta lacks certain enzymatic capabilities and relies on other organs for hormone synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following substances is formed specifically by the fetal liver during pregnancy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["16-alpha-hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone","Oestriol","16-alpha-hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone sulfate","Dehydroepiandrosterone sulfate","Pregnenolone"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe fetal liver specifically produces \u003Cstrong\u003E16-alpha-hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone sulfate\u003C/strong\u003E by hydroxylating dehydroepiandrosterone sulfate. This is a crucial step in the production of pregnancy oestrogens.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E16-alpha-hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by desulfation of 16-alpha-hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone sulfate in the placenta\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOestriol\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by the placenta from 16-alpha-hydroxydehydroepiandrosterone\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDehydroepiandrosterone sulfate\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by the maternal and fetal adrenal glands\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPregnenolone\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by both maternal and fetal tissues from cholesterol\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe placenta lacks the ability to perform 16-alpha hydroxylation, making fetal liver participation essential for oestrogen synthesis during pregnancy. This represents a key example of fetal-placental cooperation in hormone production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The fetal liver hydroxylates dehydroepiandrosterone sulfate (DHEA-S) at the 16-alpha position as part of placental oestrogen synthesis.","The placenta cannot perform 16-alpha hydroxylation, requiring fetal liver participation in oestrogen production.","This fetal-placental cooperation is essential for producing oestriol, the main oestrogen during pregnancy."],"references":["Lotto J, Stephan TL, Hoodless PA. Fetal liver development and implications for liver disease pathogenesis. Nat Rev Gastroenterol Hepatol. 2023 Sep;20(9):561-581. doi: 10.1038/s41575-023-00775-2. Epub 2023 May 19. PMID: 37208503.","Shen LH, Fan L, Zhang Y, Zhu YK, Zong XL, Peng GN, Cao SZ. Protective Effect and Mechanism of Placenta Extract on Liver. Nutrients. 2022 Nov 29;14(23):5071. doi: 10.3390/nu14235071. PMID: 36501102; PMCID: PMC9737791.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57529"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15895"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57529","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57529"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T22:11:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T22:13:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8586"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72059"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","positio